cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.SI. 

The paper proposes a novel algorithm for unsupervised learning of timeseries data using deep learning techniques. The algorithm integrates dimensionality reduction and temporal clustering into a single end-to-end learning framework. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). However, given the focus on deep learning and unsupervised learning of timeseries data, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories. The use of visualization methods to gain insight into the learned features also suggests a potential fit with cs.CV. The consideration of different similarity metrics for temporal clustering could also align with cs.NE and cs.SI.
